\f1\b0\fs28 \cf0 1. Launch TextEdit.\
2. Select "Edit/Input/Hexadecimal Input" menu item.  The input mode palette window should be displayed (note: Cmd+Ctrl+Space will toggle between Cocoa input system & the native input system).\
3. Select "H" button in the palette (note: Ctrl-X will toggle between the Alphabet Input and Hexidecimal input items).\
A hexadecimal input box will appear. \
4. Use Ctrl-F (forward) or Ctrl-B (backward) to increment or decrement the hexidecimal input, or simply type in a hexidecimal number. The HexInputServer will display the corresponding unicode character in your document.\
